

Edit Purchase Order Number <%=@po.po_number%>
<br>
<br>
<form method="post" action="/purchase_orders/edit/<%=@po.id%>">
<input id="hidden" type="hidden" name="_method" value="patch">
<label>PO Authorized Amount: <input type="text" id="edit_po_auth_amount" name="po[:po_number]" value="<%=@po.po_authorized_amount%>"></label>
<br>
<br>
Change to another existing vendor (current vendor selected by default):
<br>
  <select id="list_of_vendors" name="po[vendor_id]">
    <%Vendor.all.each do |v|%>
    <option value="<%=v.id%>" <%="selected" if v.id == @po.vendor.id%>><%=v.name.capitalize%></option>
    <%end%>
  </select>
  <br>
<br>
Change to another existing budget (current budget selected by default):
<br>
  <select id="list_of_budgets" name="po[budget_id]">
    <%Budget.all.each do |b|%>
    <option value="<%=b.id%>" <%="selected" if b.id == @po.budget.id%>><%=b.name.capitalize%></option>
    <%end%>
  </select>
  <br>
<br>
Create new vendor to assign to PO:
<br>
<label>Vendor Name:<input type="text" id="new_vendor" name="vendor[name]"></label>
<br>
<br>
Create new budget to assign to PO:
<br>
<label>Budget Name:<input type="text" id="new_budget_name" name="budget[name]"></label>
<br>
<label>Budget Target:<input type="text" id="new_budget_target" name="budget[target]"></label>
<br>
<br>
<input type="submit" value="Update Purchase Order!">
</form>